        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 55-year-old woman from the Czech Republic who comes in looking tired and uncomfortable, frequently resting a hand over the upper abdomen as she describes ongoing abdominal pain and a pressure-like discomfort after meals [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:0]. She reports nausea with intermittent vomiting, especially around eating, and says she has become troubled by bloating and excessive belching over the last few weeks [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]. She also notes early satiety and reduced appetite, saying that she feels full quickly and has been eating smaller portions than usual [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:1].\n\nIn daily life, {patientName} works as an administrative assistant and usually enjoys a steady routine, but recently she has been distracted at work by stomach discomfort and the need to avoid heavier meals. She likes meeting friends for coffee and rich café foods, though she has noticed that coffee and fatty meals seem to worsen her symptoms, so she has started cutting back [MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]. She lives with her husband, keeps in close contact with her adult daughter, and spends weekends cooking for family, although lately even the smell of heavy food can make her feel queasy [SNOMED:K29.7].\n\nShe describes herself as generally active but not athletic, preferring neighborhood walks and light gardening. Over the past month she has avoided social dinners because eating often leads to bloating, belching, and a sensation of upper abdominal fullness [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]. She is worried that the symptoms are persisting, but she is reassured by being able to talk clearly, with no signs of acute distress beyond discomfort from abdominal inflammation-related symptoms [SNOMED:K29.7]."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:4d13d33a-29c5-45d3-b0ad-ba3c3426d7dd",
      "resource": {
