          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} reports several weeks of upper abdominal discomfort with nausea, bloating, belching, and occasional vomiting after food [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]. She says the discomfort is worse after coffee and heavier, fatty meals, so she has recently tried to avoid these triggers [MEDDIALOG:K29.7:0, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]. She denies alcohol misuse and has not been taking ibuprofen after hearing that it may aggravate gastritis [MEDDIALOG:K29.7:3].\n\nShe has not had prior major hospitalizations and has no known chronic gastrointestinal diagnosis documented. Her recent symptoms have led to decreased appetite and smaller meals because of early satiety and fear of provoking nausea or vomiting [SNOMED:K29.7, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:1]. She has no reported prior abdominal surgery. Lifestyle-wise, she drinks coffee regularly, eats a mixed diet, and is now attempting more bland foods because dietary change is commonly advised in gastritis [MEDDIALOG:K29.7:0, MEDDIALOG:K29.7:4]."
          }
        ]
      }
